iajoiner commented on a change in pull request #12231:
URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/12231#discussion_r790289895



##########
File path: cpp/src/arrow/adapters/orc/adapter.cc
##########
@@ -720,11 +720,7 @@ class ArrowOutputStream : public liborc::OutputStream {
     return filename;
   }

-  void close() override {
-    if (!output_stream_.closed()) {
-      ORC_THROW_NOT_OK(output_stream_.Close());
-    }
-  }
+  void close() override {}

Review comment:
       What ORC does is writing the content. Then it attempts to close the `liborc::OutputStream.` https://github.com/apache/orc/blob/7e12a8ccac81548fde6e5d0538da2e68c77df601/c%2B%2B/src/Writer.cc#L369
   
   The issue here is of course that we shouldn’t actually close the `arrow::io::OutputStream` because at least in some instances (such as when we are using `io.BytesIO`) where we don’t exactly want it closed right after the flushing.




